page.title: 11Wild life
page.content: {WILD LIFE }Everything that lives in the forest is wild life, like badgers, hedgehogs, squirrels, hares, snakes, rabbits, foxes and wild birds like the blue tit and the robin.{I saw a horse {and birds.}Some squirrels were running up trees.{There is a lot of wild life {in the forest, ponies, donkeys and {cows.}Wild life is wonderful.{You can {often see deer. Kevin Baulf 8. }You can see the animals foot prints in the ground. {Elizabeth Yarde 8. }There is a lot of wild life in our area, moles, long eared bats, red and fallow deer, rabbits, thrushes, housemartins, long tailed tits, chaffinches, swallows and blackbirds. {Peter Bennison 8.}There is lots of wild life in the forest, there are loads of ponies on the heath and loads of squirrels in the trees. {Glenn Cartwright,8 Russell Thorne,8 {Paul Bran,8.
